==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Disintegration
<hw>Dis*in`te*gra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>The process by which anything is disintegrated; the condition of
anything which is disintegrated.</def> Specifically <sd>(b)</sd>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>The wearing away or falling to pieces of rocks
or strata, produced by atmospheric action, frost, ice, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Society had need of further <qex>disintegration</qex> before it
could begin to reconstruct itself locally.</q>
<rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disintegrator</ent>⟦br⟧
